lenders.loan_because:
In English:
Hi, a little over 02 years ago I was diagnosed with tendinitis in my right hand because the work use the computer mouse . I was wearing rehabilitation therapies which must be accompanied by medical break though, because my delivery job kept my attendance at work and despite the pain continued to work . Last year of therapy and pain medications are increasingly stressed . I made thousands of tests until the doctor who treated me decided to have surgery . My operation was initially estimated to finish in 60 minutes via laparoscopy however, to get into my hands that were complicated and had to become a much larger cut and put me 02 nails sticking out of my hand . I left the operating room 05 hours later.
I went through a lot, I was hospitalized a week at the clinic. When I register a whole ordeal since having any exposed nails scraping or involuntary movement generated immense pain . One week later my hand started to swell, became purple color, my nails darkened color and I sprouted beautiful thick and large . I went to my doctor and was diagnosed with reflex sympathetic dystrophy . Few people have heard of it because it is a neurological reaction that gives off very few people ( Bingo! I went one of them) . The fact is that from that day can not work. This month turned operated one year and I could not resume my activities and therefore I can not generate income. Expenses claim my medications , medical interventions ( pain blocking ) , medical appointments , physical rehabilitation, psychological rehabilitation , therapy pool, implements rehabilitation at home, etc. .. are very high.

If you require it , as I support everything I have written above lines . My profile picture is a sample of my hand weeks after surgery.
---------
In Spanish:
Hola, hace un poco más de 02 años me diagnosticaron tendinitis en mi mano derecha por uso del mouse del computador. Estuve llevando terapias de rehabilitación las cuales debieron estar acompañadas de descanso médico sin embargo, debido a mi entrega en el trabajo mantuve mi asistencia al trabajo y a pesar de los dolores continuaba trabajando. Pasado el año de terapias y medicinas el dolor se acentuaba cada vez más. Me hicieron miles de exámenes hasta que el doctor que me trataba decidió operarme. Mi operación inicialmente estaba estimada en terminar en 60 minutos y vía paroscopía sin embargo, al ingresar a mi mano las cosas se complicaron y tuvieron que hacerme un corte mucho más grande y colocarme 02 clavos que sobresalían de mi mano. Salí de sala de operaciones 05 horas después.
Pasé por mucho, estuve internada una semana en la clínica. Al darme de alta todo un calvario ya que al tener los clavos expuestos cualquier roce o movimiento involuntario generaba un dolor inmenso. Pasados los días mi mano comenzó a inflamarse, se tornó de color morada, mis uñas se oscurecieron de color y me brotaron bellos gruesos y grandes. Acudí a mi médico y me diagnosticó Distrofia simpática refleja. Pocos son los que han oido hablar de ello ya que es una reacción neurológica que le da a poquísimas personas (Bingo! Yo fuí una de ellas). El hecho está en que desde aquel día no puedo trabajar. Este mes cumplí un año de operada y aún no he podido retomar mis actividades y por ende no puedo generar ingresos. Los gastos que demandan mis medicinas, intervenciones médicas (bloqueos de dolor), citas médicas, rehabilitación física, rehabilitación psicológica, terapia en piscina, implementos para rehabilitación en casa, etc..son muy altos.

Si usted lo requieren, tengo como sustentar todo lo que he escrito lineas arriba. Mi foto de perfil es una muestra de mi mano semanas después de operada.

“Why Should I Buy Land ”is a question our team at CrownWorld get asked every day, so we thought it worthwhile to have a closer look at some of the reasons in this week’s blog post.
Land is tangible. It is a real physical asset that appreciates over time, proving a solid consistent hedge against inflation and not some imaginary financial instrument.
Land is precious and the supply is finite. As Mark Twain succinctly put it. “Buy Land, they’re not making it anymore”.
Land is a great foundation for wealth creation. Wealthy families worldwide have built their fortunes through land holdings-you don’t get rich from rental income, capital appreciation is the driver.
Land ownership diversifies your investment portfolio. The days of securing your retirement by solely investing in the stock market are long gone. Recent changes in UK pension legislation acknowledge that considered diversification is the key to a comfortable old age.
Land ownership is a low-cost stepping stone to real estate wealth. Enter the lucrative real estate market at a fraction of the cost rather than saving for large cash deposits required for full property ownership. Take further advantage of CrownWorld’s non–statuszero interest finance plan and international real estate investment becomes even more accessible with as little as a few thousand dollars upfront payment.
Land Investment may not have been something you have seriously considered before, but the vast majority of Real Estate Funds now have more than half of their holdings in development land- and the reason is simple.
As recessionary fears subside as real estate markets recover reflected in rising prices, it’s the land value proportion of the property that inflates, not the price of bricks! In short, land acquisition with full planning is where the smart money is going. Considerable capital appreciation potential but at a fraction of the investment cost.
